1
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:38,664
Do you, Jon Jonsson,

2
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:44,075
take Thora to be your
lawful wedded wife?

3
00:00:49,015 --> 00:00:50,141
Yes.

4
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:53,851
Will you, with God's help,
be faithful to her,

5
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:59,917
honor and respect her
through all that God may bring?

6
00:00:59,959 --> 00:01:01,017
Yeah, sure.

7
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:08,591
Do you, Thora Larusdottir,

8
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:12,935
take Jon to be
your lawful wedded...

9
00:01:12,972 --> 00:01:13,996
Yes.

10
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:15,337
...husband?
- Yes

11
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:20,202
The rings are a token
of your love and devotion.

12
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,012
It's the left hand.

13
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:38,054
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

14
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,066
You may kiss the bride.

15
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:52,707
Jon...

16
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:55,744
Excuse me,
I have to take this.

17
00:01:57,317 --> 00:01:59,148
Jon! It's Dad.

18
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:00,979
Dad...

19
00:02:01,020 --> 00:02:04,387
Your mother is completely lost.

20
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:07,825
- Where did you say we were?
- Kerlingarskard.

21
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:12,231
Dad, hold on a second...
Can we proceed?

22
00:02:12,765 --> 00:02:14,323
- You may kiss the bride.
- Right.

23
00:02:15,768 --> 00:02:16,928
Dad, I'll call you back.

24
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,631
We've just gone
a little bit too far...

25
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:22,701
You have no idea where we are.

26
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:26,836
I'm in the church.
I have to kiss the bride.

27
00:02:28,047 --> 00:02:32,507
You said Midsummer night.
That's tomorrow.

28
00:02:32,552 --> 00:02:35,282
It's a rehearsal.
I'll call back later.

29
00:02:37,423 --> 00:02:38,549
Sorry.

30
00:02:39,692 --> 00:02:40,750
Mom, stop it.

31
00:02:40,793 --> 00:02:43,261
- I didn't say a word!
- Just stop it.

32
00:02:43,296 --> 00:02:44,763
Where were we?

33
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,290
You may kiss the bride.

34
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:48,300
Thanks.

35
00:02:57,911 --> 00:02:59,105
...and all that.

36
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:00,744
What did he say?

37
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:04,944
He was in the church...
rehearsing.

38
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:06,915
Rehearsing?

39
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:09,745
It's not like he is doing it
for the first time.

40
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:49,755
On one hand we have
the persona of the doctor,

41
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:51,757
the honest man.

42
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:54,760
In his mind there are no 'ifs' -

43
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:59,027
It is simply wrong
to betray your wife.

44
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:03,363
That's the moral 'absolutism'
of Kant.

45
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:08,363
Betrayal is wrong...

46
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:10,706
No matter what
the circumstances.

47
00:05:14,447 --> 00:05:16,915
The other guy thinks
he's doing what's best,

48
00:05:16,949 --> 00:05:18,644
what leads to the best consequences.

49
00:05:18,685 --> 00:05:20,175
It's possible.

50
00:05:20,219 --> 00:05:23,450
The end justifies the means
is the author's point then?

51
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:27,983
We shouldn't assume
we know the author's point...

52
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:31,793
but we definitely
have two opposites.

53
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:36,734
The doctor and then
the protagonist, the landowner,

54
00:05:36,769 --> 00:05:43,140
who betrays his wife
in hope of a better life.

55
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:46,907
A consequientialist, if you will...

56
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:49,915
The end justifies the means.

57
00:05:49,949 --> 00:05:55,717
We could also define it
as graded absolutism.

58
00:05:55,755 --> 00:06:01,489
Things aren't right or wrong,
as the doctor says.

59
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:04,724
They are relatively wrong
or relatively right,

60
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:08,200
depending on the circumstances.

61
00:06:08,234 --> 00:06:13,035
It is wrong to steal,
but worse to starve your child.

62
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:44,662
The landowner
intends to save his life

63
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:47,036
even if it means
he has to betray his wife.

64
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:52,773
To save a man's life,
in this case his own,

65
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:57,840
is more important to him
than being faithful to his wife.

66
00:06:58,317 --> 00:07:01,286
Does it have to be
so complicated?

67
00:07:02,655 --> 00:07:04,885
Isn't love always justifiable?

68
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:07,358
That's an oversimplification...

69
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:10,061
I just think your explanation

70
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,326
is unnecessarily
long and complicated.

71
00:07:16,135 --> 00:07:20,731
Maybe you are right,
perhaps it is...

72
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:24,209
long and unnecessary.

73
00:07:44,897 --> 00:07:46,125
Do you need saving?

74
00:07:46,165 --> 00:07:48,030
What?
No. I'm safe.

75
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:49,557
Are you sure?

76
00:07:49,602 --> 00:07:50,626
Sure of what?

77
00:07:51,537 --> 00:07:52,765
My love

78
00:08:05,952 --> 00:08:06,919
Yes?

79
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:09,677
Why don't you answer?

80
00:08:09,722 --> 00:08:11,155
The phone was off.
What is it?

81
00:08:11,724 --> 00:08:13,715
Oh, God...

82
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:14,953
I had an accident.

83
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:15,961
An accident?

84
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:18,896
I didn't see him,
I was driving and...

85
00:08:18,931 --> 00:08:20,626
Calm down, Anna.

86
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,361
Don't start with that.
I am calm.

87
00:08:22,401 --> 00:08:24,028
I was driving down...

88
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:26,402
I can't hear you when you shout.

89
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:30,739
I am not shouting!
Just listen to me - I hit a swan!

90
00:08:30,776 --> 00:08:33,836
- Hit what?
- Or a goose or something!

91
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,747
A swan? A bird?
And are you all right?

92
00:08:37,316 --> 00:08:38,943
Yes, but...

93
00:08:40,086 --> 00:08:41,553
Could I have a quick word?

94
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:43,447
You're all right, aren't you?

95
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:46,849
Yes, I'm fine.

96
00:08:53,332 --> 00:08:56,995
All right, darling.
See you when I get home.

97
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,129
Bye, sweetheart.

98
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:12,749
Thank you, Reverend.

99
00:09:13,486 --> 00:09:15,454
Well, say your goodbyes for now.

100
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:17,079
Yes.

101
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:19,921
- You'll make the house cozy for us?
- Sure.

102
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:22,086
And you can't see me
until tomorrow.

103
00:09:22,428 --> 00:09:23,861
Makes it more fun.

104
00:09:26,465 --> 00:09:29,263
It'll be just like the first time.

105
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:40,868
- Tell him to come and see me.
- I will. Just take it easy.

106
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:43,871
Mom!

107
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:49,052
Sisi wants you to stop by today.

108
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:51,283
We have to settle things
before the wedding.

109
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:56,053
I have to pick up
a friend from the ferry.

110
00:09:56,963 --> 00:09:59,022
We're just waiting
for that subsidy.

111
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:01,033
That's great,
see you later today then.

112
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:04,400
Come in through the kitchen
so Thora won't run into you.

113
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,404
Right.

114
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:13,409
Thanks...
See you tomorrow.

115
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:16,905
I suppose so.

116
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:49,367
Thanks for dinner.

117
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,969
Wild game?

118
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:14,059
- Anna...
- I want to go home.

119
00:12:15,534 --> 00:12:18,230
- What do you mean?
- Home.

120
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:48,991
I love you.

121
00:12:52,671 --> 00:12:55,231
For having the courage.

122
00:12:56,675 --> 00:12:58,643
For sacrificing.

123
00:13:04,383 --> 00:13:06,180
Sacrificing?

124
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:10,088
Resigning and starting all over again.

125
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,590
Hi, Malla. Are you sure
you picked the right numbers?

126
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:55,361
I'm not talking to you.
You're bad luck.

127
00:13:57,636 --> 00:13:59,570
Congratulations on the new wife.

128
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:00,697
Thanks.

129
00:14:00,739 --> 00:14:02,366
Coming on strong into second- half!

130
00:14:02,408 --> 00:14:04,774
It was time to get back into the game.

131
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:06,710
How much younger than you?

132
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:10,875
- Eighteen years.
- Ouch, you're such a bad boy!

133
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:15,214
She is an old soul
and I'm young at heart.

134
00:14:16,288 --> 00:14:18,313
So no hope there either?

135
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,984
You haven't changed a bit.

136
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,721
- You're graying.
- And you've lost weight.

137
00:14:22,761 --> 00:14:24,194
- Do you think so?
- No.

138
00:14:25,731 --> 00:14:27,665
All dressed up already?

139
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,601
The wedding is tomorrow.
We're not going to sleep, are we?

140
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:34,066
- No luggage?
- What for?

141
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:40,277
- Get in.
- Wow, nice!

142
00:14:40,312 --> 00:14:42,507
There are no cars on the island.

143
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:45,415
- Do you think it will hold?
- Sure. It's American.

144
00:14:45,451 --> 00:14:48,420
Made for heavyweight
burger bottoms.

145
00:14:50,823 --> 00:14:52,381
Take it easy though.

146
00:14:54,126 --> 00:14:55,889
Thanks for coming.

147
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:58,761
Somebody has to play the organ
at your wedding.

148
00:14:58,797 --> 00:15:00,424
What are you playing?

149
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:02,525
I don't know, maybe...

150
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:06,197
He's got the gray hair blues!

151
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:10,265
He's got the gray hair blues...

152
00:15:24,823 --> 00:15:28,725
- Who's the nutter?
- Who? Malla?

153
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,922
I saw her spend a fortune
on lottery tickets.

154
00:15:30,963 --> 00:15:32,396
She's kind of fixed
on the lottery.

155
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:33,989
She's a freak!

156
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,397
- Freak!
- Stop it!

157
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,667
- You're staying at my place.
- Oh?

158
00:15:40,706 --> 00:15:45,075
Thora is staying at
her mother's guesthouse tonight.

159
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:47,442
Already staying at her mother's?

160
00:15:47,479 --> 00:15:50,073
It's a tradition.
I can't see her until the wedding.

161
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:51,905
Cute...

162
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:56,251
So we can share
a few old stories.

163
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:58,415
We sure can.

164
00:15:58,457 --> 00:16:00,357
Remember the year
we left college?

165
00:16:00,392 --> 00:16:01,416
Yeah.

166
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:04,361
Must have been the same year
your wife got potty trained.

167
00:16:17,176 --> 00:16:21,806
So your roots lie here in Flatey,
like mine?

168
00:16:21,847 --> 00:16:24,145
My parents grew up here.

169
00:16:24,183 --> 00:16:27,983
So you're related to
Anna of Hvammur,

170
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:33,048
who was married to Gudberg,
father of Asberg the magistrate,

171
00:16:33,092 --> 00:16:39,793
who married Gudfinna and
then later her sister Gudmunda!

172
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:41,322
That's possible.

173
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:44,200
I'll say. Welcome back home, cousin.

174
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:49,201
If there is anything I can do
just let me know.

175
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:54,235
I have plenty of time
to attend to my parish.

176
00:16:54,279 --> 00:16:55,473
Thank you.

177
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:58,745
And you know about
the collection box.

178
00:16:58,784 --> 00:17:01,753
We are raising money
to fix the altarpiece...

179
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:10,522
My piano!
It's here!

180
00:17:19,838 --> 00:17:21,465
Good day to you all.

181
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:37,916
Howdy, Reverend.

182
00:17:38,657 --> 00:17:39,919
Thanks so much.

183
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:41,983
Faith moves mountains.
I take care of the rest.

184
00:17:45,831 --> 00:17:47,628
I've got to get going.

185
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,896
- Reverend!
- Yes.

186
00:17:51,270 --> 00:17:52,532
A new helmet?

187
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,205
Pure ecstasy.

188
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:26,933
I'll only be a minute.

189
00:18:27,706 --> 00:18:29,173
Do they sell cigarettes here?

190
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,573
I think so.

191
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:58,429
Jesus Christ!

192
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:03,396
I'm sorry...
Larus said you wanted to see me.

193
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:08,377
What is there to discuss?

194
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:11,673
Unless you're here
to pay your debt.

195
00:19:12,784 --> 00:19:16,948
- I was about to bring that up.
- Really?

196
00:19:18,524 --> 00:19:22,927
- Are four jars of jam enough?
- No, it's not enough!

197
00:19:23,195 --> 00:19:26,221
Tell Thora to stay out of the kitchen
while Jon is here.

198
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:28,626
Right.

199
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:36,901
- Want to buy something?
- Just cigarettes.

200
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:38,868
How many?

201
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:41,675
Many? Two packets.

202
00:19:46,318 --> 00:19:48,548
Two times twenty...

203
00:19:51,823 --> 00:19:53,654
You do sell cigarettes in packets,
don't you?

204
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:58,187
Just taking down
the numbers you use.

205
00:19:58,230 --> 00:19:58,924
1200.

206
00:19:58,964 --> 00:20:00,295
What? 1200?

207
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:08,206
Wow!
What's your shoe size?

208
00:20:10,008 --> 00:20:11,669
Fifty, why?

209
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:13,936
Half and half is one.

210
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:17,007
- Excuse me?
- A meter.

211
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,073
What?

212
00:20:18,116 --> 00:20:21,347
Each foot is half a meter
so together they are one meter.

213
00:20:23,422 --> 00:20:24,480
Freak.

214
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,456
The tourist board...

215
00:20:30,495 --> 00:20:31,587
Have you lost your mind?

216
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:33,120
...promised us a subsidy.

217
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,531
If you think you can
take advantage of us

218
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:38,297
the day before
marrying my daughter!

219
00:20:38,337 --> 00:20:39,736
This is not the best time...

220
00:20:39,771 --> 00:20:41,329
This is completely unacceptable.

221
00:20:41,373 --> 00:20:46,675
I am trying to run a business.
I was expecting this money.

222
00:20:53,685 --> 00:20:58,213
Any decent man
would have settled the debt

223
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,225
before proposing to my daughter!

224
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:03,087
Is it such a big deal?

225
00:21:03,128 --> 00:21:06,586
Honor our agreement
or I'll get a lawyer.

226
00:21:07,232 --> 00:21:09,700
Why not get someone
to rough me up, make me pay?

227
00:21:10,702 --> 00:21:13,535
I'll do it if I have to.

228
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:17,670
If you don't pay by tomorrow...

229
00:21:17,709 --> 00:21:21,509
the wedding will be called off!

230
00:21:24,216 --> 00:21:28,778
- Is everything all right?
- I'm having a hard time breathing.

231
00:21:29,588 --> 00:21:32,182
- I'm sorry, I just...
- Mom!

232
00:21:37,496 --> 00:21:41,728
He seduces our daughter
and then tries to swindle us.

233
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:46,261
- That womanizer from hell.
- What's going on?

234
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,567
Ask your father!

235
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:53,677
Hello...

236
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:56,474
Yes, I can hear you.

237
00:21:59,184 --> 00:22:02,779
What? I can't hear you now.

238
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:04,288
Dad?

239
00:22:07,559 --> 00:22:08,787
Damn!

240
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:14,799
Do you mind
if I smoke in the car?

241
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:15,800
Suit yourself.

242
00:23:26,037 --> 00:23:28,938
Nine holes?
A golf course has eighteen, right?

243
00:23:29,608 --> 00:23:32,270
It's half a course.
You just go two rounds.

244
00:23:33,612 --> 00:23:35,477
This is quite a project?

245
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:39,883
Not that big -
thirty, forty maybe.

246
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:41,715
- Thirty, forty?
- Million.

247
00:23:42,854 --> 00:23:47,882
You'll get your money back
in about five years and after that,

248
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:50,053
pure ecstasy.

249
00:23:51,997 --> 00:23:55,933
You start on the reef,
hit over to the second hole.

250
00:23:56,868 --> 00:23:59,894
This is the graveyard,
two bunkers, sand traps...

251
00:24:00,338 --> 00:24:02,738
So you have to shoot
over the graveyard?

252
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:07,643
Or over the church.
No challenge, no fun!

253
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:13,749
The third hole
is on Lalli and Sisi's land.

254
00:24:13,785 --> 00:24:15,082
Lalli and Sisi?

255
00:24:15,887 --> 00:24:17,115
Sisi and Lalli.

256
00:24:24,996 --> 00:24:27,157
That's our land, isn't it?

257
00:24:27,599 --> 00:24:30,966
That's the idea.
Jon will be renting your land.

258
00:24:31,736 --> 00:24:34,671
- Me?
- Really?

259
00:24:34,706 --> 00:24:36,401
Isn't that so?

260
00:24:37,609 --> 00:24:41,375
Well, a man has got
to keep himself busy, right?

261
00:24:41,646 --> 00:24:47,346
He'll cut the grass for you,
you get the hay and also the rent.

262
00:24:47,385 --> 00:24:52,118
The guesthouse fills up with golfers
and everybody profits!

263
00:24:53,124 --> 00:24:55,354
We have to make a toast to that!

264
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:00,624
What do you think you're doing?

265
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:04,328
Put it on Jon's tab.
We have to celebrate.

266
00:25:04,369 --> 00:25:05,700
Jon's tab?

267
00:25:07,439 --> 00:25:08,906
Pure ecstasy.

268
00:25:14,646 --> 00:25:15,772
It's a birdie!

269
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:21,751
What a stupid place
to start a golf course.

270
00:25:23,788 --> 00:25:25,813
This isn't for beginners, you know.

271
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:34,064
I've been trying to help Jon
make some money.

272
00:25:34,099 --> 00:25:36,932
But no, he won't have that.

273
00:25:36,968 --> 00:25:40,734
- Why don't you want to make money?
- We're getting there.

274
00:25:40,772 --> 00:25:45,300
Getting where?
So when do I get paid?

275
00:25:45,343 --> 00:25:52,511
- Pay you?
- We have to advertise, put up a website.

276
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:55,520
When we get the subsidy.

277
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:59,922
Grants and handouts!
Just like in the Soviet, Comrade Jon.

278
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:05,128
He's against tourists.
They are the future.

279
00:26:09,935 --> 00:26:15,032
- What are you doing, darling?
- Just touching up the wedding dress.

280
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:18,770
- Do you like it?
- It's nice.

281
00:26:26,051 --> 00:26:29,987
It feels like I just got married yesterday.
How time flies.

282
00:26:30,021 --> 00:26:33,980
Your dad was so cute, tall and thin.

283
00:26:36,361 --> 00:26:38,352
We were so young.

284
00:26:43,501 --> 00:26:47,062
Doing everything together,
the first apartment,

285
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:48,902
our first loan.

286
00:27:00,352 --> 00:27:04,049
Darling, are you sure
you're doing the right thing?

287
00:27:06,791 --> 00:27:13,720
You're missing out on so much.
Just stepping into his old life.

288
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:18,099
I don't have to do everything like you.
It's not the only way.

289
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:20,764
- The man is turning gray.
- So what?

290
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:24,172
Maybe it's all right now.
But then you get to my age.

291
00:27:25,276 --> 00:27:29,235
- What about children?
- Stop it, please.

292
00:27:33,284 --> 00:27:35,377
I'm close to blowing
the whole thing off.

293
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:38,753
What's wrong with you?
You can't cancel my wedding.

294
00:27:38,790 --> 00:27:41,350
We'll just go to Reykjavik
and get married there.

295
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:55,139
What did I say wrong now?

296
00:27:59,911 --> 00:28:04,245
We have enough goddamn tourists.
Naked Germans all over the place.

297
00:28:05,216 --> 00:28:06,979
There's more of them
than the bloody sheep.

298
00:28:07,018 --> 00:28:09,316
Hairy old German hags
in every hotspring.

299
00:28:10,255 --> 00:28:12,450
We can just as well
skin them, can't we?

300
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:14,825
Skin the hide of their backs!

301
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:17,157
You guys are lacking...

302
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:21,859
What do you call it?
Entre... preneur... thing!

303
00:28:24,269 --> 00:28:26,032
Entrepreneurship!

304
00:28:26,938 --> 00:28:28,599
That's what I said!

305
00:28:29,674 --> 00:28:32,837
I may not have a diploma
to wipe up my ass

306
00:28:32,877 --> 00:28:38,144
but I've sure got...
the entrepreneur... shit working.

307
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:42,213
Please give me some
of that entrepreneurshit!

308
00:28:47,759 --> 00:28:50,853
Start by taking a sea bath.

309
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:57,266
Learn to swim,
to get rid of that lifesaver.

310
00:28:57,302 --> 00:28:59,270
Don't get him all worked up.

311
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:04,035
It's freezing!

312
00:29:04,476 --> 00:29:06,444
Just wait for the tide.

313
00:29:31,636 --> 00:29:35,663
- Guys...
- What?

314
00:29:36,174 --> 00:29:38,301
- I can't find...
- What?

315
00:29:38,676 --> 00:29:41,201
I can't find...

316
00:29:41,246 --> 00:29:43,305
my willy.

317
00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:46,644
It's gone!

318
00:29:46,684 --> 00:29:48,379
Free Willy!

319
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:01,493
- Hi, darling.
- Hi.

320
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:04,001
- Still awake?
- Just blogging.

321
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:10,733
- I just wanted to say good night.
- Good night.

322
00:30:13,411 --> 00:30:18,348
- Is something wrong?
- No, just...

323
00:30:18,383 --> 00:30:22,080
- Just what?
- Nothing.

324
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:26,287
- All right, good night then.
- Dad?

325
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:27,450
Yes.

326
00:30:33,131 --> 00:30:34,894
It's just Jon...

327
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,634
He's been acting strange lately.

328
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:45,336
What if he... doesn't love me?

329
00:30:48,279 --> 00:30:50,338
My dear little girl.

330
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:53,813
Don't get mad, but...

331
00:30:57,488 --> 00:31:01,424
it's been such a short time since Anna.

332
00:31:03,628 --> 00:31:06,096
And he's so much older than you.

333
00:31:06,130 --> 00:31:08,325
Why is it impossible
to talk to you all?

334
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:11,563
He's having a hard time
and he needs me.

335
00:31:11,603 --> 00:31:13,332
But you don't need him.

336
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:16,033
I've made up my mind.
I'm marrying him.

337
00:31:17,508 --> 00:31:19,738
I've known it
since I first met him.

338
00:31:28,019 --> 00:31:34,083
Well, darling, of course
you have to follow your heart.

339
00:31:34,125 --> 00:31:37,993
- Yes, of course.
- Right.

340
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:46,199
What was I thinking?

341
00:32:30,615 --> 00:32:34,642
- The terns are quiet tonight.
- Yes... Thank you.

342
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:39,957
- Are all the drawings yours?
- Yes.

343
00:32:40,858 --> 00:32:43,656
Well, they're really...

344
00:32:43,695 --> 00:32:47,153
really... something.

345
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:12,213
Are you going to pay or not?

346
00:33:12,256 --> 00:33:15,089
- Not now, later.
- We want our money now.

347
00:33:15,126 --> 00:33:18,061
No money, money tomorrow,
plenty of money tomorrow.

348
00:33:18,096 --> 00:33:19,063
Wait a moment.

349
00:33:19,097 --> 00:33:21,463
- Bloody hell!
- Bloody hell yourself!

350
00:33:21,799 --> 00:33:24,131
- Help me out here?
- What do you want me to say?

351
00:33:24,769 --> 00:33:27,602
Just something.
You're a professor.

352
00:33:28,072 --> 00:33:30,040
Isn't that what you
do for a living?

353
00:33:30,074 --> 00:33:33,737
Hey, Polish guys, talk to my friend.
He is the boss.

354
00:33:33,978 --> 00:33:36,503
Careful, it's brand new!

355
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:46,486
- Are you paying us, Mr. Big Boss?
- It's a little bit...

356
00:33:46,524 --> 00:33:50,187
- Hi! Is everything all right?
- One moment.

357
00:33:51,829 --> 00:33:53,626
Yeah, fine!

358
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:57,433
- Hi...
- Thora.

359
00:33:57,468 --> 00:33:59,595
- Yes, Thora...
- Don't you remember me?

360
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:04,441
- Yeah sure... from...
- From your class.

361
00:34:04,475 --> 00:34:06,943
- What are you doing here?
- Coming to your rescue.

362
00:34:07,745 --> 00:34:08,871
Just kidding.

363
00:34:10,548 --> 00:34:14,780
- We've got everything.
- OK. Dad's picking us up.

364
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:21,651
- Are you in a band?
- Not really, I'm a groupie.

365
00:34:23,361 --> 00:34:26,228
They're playing
at the guesthouse tonight.

366
00:34:26,931 --> 00:34:29,866
- You should come, they're really good.
- Yeah.

367
00:34:31,903 --> 00:34:33,268
Darling!

368
00:34:37,341 --> 00:34:38,569
Do you know each other?

369
00:34:38,609 --> 00:34:40,440
He was my teacher
at the University.

370
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,911
This lad is the best thing
that has landed on this island.

371
00:34:43,948 --> 00:34:45,313
Lad! How cute.

372
00:34:46,684 --> 00:34:49,209
He's opening a golf course.

373
00:34:49,253 --> 00:34:51,687
And he has promised us
a lot of golfers this summer.

374
00:34:51,722 --> 00:34:55,624
- A golf course? No kidding!
- Actually, it's not a joke.

375
00:34:55,660 --> 00:34:59,528
- Jon, help me out here.
- We want money now or we go.

376
00:35:05,636 --> 00:35:09,163
Guys, please, one more day.

377
00:35:09,207 --> 00:35:11,175
I will pay you tomorrow.

378
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:13,775
Come on!

379
00:35:18,649 --> 00:35:22,881
Thanks a million, Jon.
You didn't say a word!

380
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:26,982
Is this the guided tour of Flatey?

381
00:35:27,024 --> 00:35:28,321
Yes.

382
00:35:34,866 --> 00:35:36,424
Welcome to Flatey!

383
00:35:36,467 --> 00:35:40,528
Almost the northest island
people are living on... in.

384
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:57,777
And here, as you can see,
we have the fish freezing plant

385
00:35:57,822 --> 00:36:02,919
where 200 people were working,
when it was working!

386
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:06,396
And here on our right
we have Mr. Mill-Jon.

387
00:36:17,942 --> 00:36:21,708
I just had a great idea.
A new piece, out of seaweed.

388
00:36:21,746 --> 00:36:29,551
It comes from the sea, you know,
the uterus of the world.

389
00:36:29,954 --> 00:36:36,757
Where all life comes from.
Mother, Mare, the sea, Maria.

390
00:36:36,794 --> 00:36:39,661
Like my old pieces
but three dimensional.

391
00:36:39,697 --> 00:36:42,962
I'll hang up a net
and let it hang, like an octopus,

392
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:49,132
or veins, new life.
Or a new planet...

393
00:36:49,974 --> 00:36:52,534
Is that really necessary?

394
00:36:54,512 --> 00:36:55,706
What?

395
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:57,344
Never mind.

396
00:37:43,961 --> 00:37:46,293
- Evening, Jon.
- Hi.

397
00:37:49,133 --> 00:37:52,398
- Is Anna not coming?
- No, she wasn't feeling well.

398
00:37:53,471 --> 00:37:58,033
- She's out of this world.
- Who? What do you mean?

399
00:37:59,977 --> 00:38:04,346
- Hildur, the girl on the saw.
- Right.

400
00:38:21,699 --> 00:38:23,599
So you've stopped teaching?

401
00:38:25,503 --> 00:38:31,806
I took a leave.

402
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:38,547
Because of your wife?

403
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:44,277
Yes...

404
00:38:45,856 --> 00:38:47,483
You could say that.

405
00:38:49,493 --> 00:38:51,654
Why did you move to Flatey?

406
00:38:51,696 --> 00:38:53,664
My wife is from here.

407
00:38:53,698 --> 00:38:56,667
We came to try something new.

408
00:39:09,714 --> 00:39:14,310
A wonderful, Icelandic folksong...

409
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,047
You should be an opera singer!

410
00:39:16,087 --> 00:39:17,816
I studied in Vienna.

411
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:22,315
- Really, then why are you here?
- To sing for you, my friend!

412
00:39:31,402 --> 00:39:33,370
Here comes Dad's tourist show.

413
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:10,672
Yes?

414
00:40:10,708 --> 00:40:12,335
I'm sorry for...

415
00:40:12,843 --> 00:40:13,935
What?

416
00:40:13,978 --> 00:40:16,538
Sorry I asked
about your wife back there.

417
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:18,548
That's all right.

418
00:40:18,582 --> 00:40:21,415
I just feel like I know you...
from school.

419
00:40:24,054 --> 00:40:26,215
- Jon.
- Yes

420
00:40:28,125 --> 00:40:31,617
Why don't you relax a little.
You're off duty.

421
00:40:33,397 --> 00:40:38,357
- Want one?
- Why not? Thanks.

422
00:40:41,572 --> 00:40:46,100
- The sunset is beautiful.
- Yes.

423
00:40:50,981 --> 00:40:54,212
I don't know what happened,
if anything at all.

424
00:40:54,251 --> 00:40:56,879
I was living a nightmare.

425
00:40:57,922 --> 00:41:02,859
Same students year after year.
Same books, same authors.

426
00:41:03,694 --> 00:41:08,188
Same questions, same answers,
and, of course, the same jokes.

427
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:12,663
I was teaching people
to teach other people -

428
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:15,433
after becoming the teachers
they never wanted to be.

429
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:17,168
Like yourself?

430
00:41:17,842 --> 00:41:19,070
Yeah, like myself.

431
00:41:19,109 --> 00:41:20,440
Bummer.

432
00:41:22,012 --> 00:41:26,642
You've worked your ass off
for years with no real results...

433
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:29,653
Exhausted, but nothing to show for it.

434
00:41:31,689 --> 00:41:35,648
I thought I couldn't love anyone
the way I love you.

435
00:41:36,694 --> 00:41:41,063
I thought I could only love myself
the way I love you.

436
00:41:41,098 --> 00:41:42,656
Where did you dig this up?

437
00:41:42,700 --> 00:41:44,497
Did you write it to your wife?

438
00:41:45,169 --> 00:41:46,500
I can't remember.

439
00:41:46,537 --> 00:41:50,268
Prick! Don't you remember
whom you loved like yourself?

440
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:06,456
- Stop it.
- I'm freezing!

441
00:42:07,258 --> 00:42:10,694
You'll wake up everyone.
Thora asked me...

442
00:42:10,728 --> 00:42:12,628
I know Malla's window.

443
00:42:15,366 --> 00:42:16,492
What?

444
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:19,025
Come down. We need your help.

445
00:42:19,069 --> 00:42:20,627
You're just making fun of me.

446
00:42:20,671 --> 00:42:21,695
I'm off to bed.

447
00:42:22,172 --> 00:42:24,197
You know me better than that!

448
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:27,939
Why isn't he
wearing any clothes?

449
00:42:29,313 --> 00:42:30,575
He fell in the sea.

450
00:42:30,614 --> 00:42:32,605
Get him some clothes
before he freezes to death.

451
00:42:32,650 --> 00:42:37,610
Out of the way.
What the hell is going on!

452
00:42:37,655 --> 00:42:39,680
I told you to stay away from Malla!

453
00:42:40,257 --> 00:42:41,485
And Jon!

454
00:42:42,927 --> 00:42:44,588
Is that the mother-in-law?

455
00:42:50,167 --> 00:42:53,762
You should be at home
thinking of a way to pay us back

456
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:56,864
instead of getting drunk
the night before your own wedding...

457
00:42:56,907 --> 00:42:59,000
If there's going to be
a wedding at all!

458
00:43:01,845 --> 00:43:04,541
Maybe you're being
a little rough on him, dear.

459
00:43:05,616 --> 00:43:07,948
Are you going to make
your daughter homeless?

460
00:43:08,552 --> 00:43:09,883
What do you mean?

461
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:12,722
He'll never pay us
once they are married.

462
00:43:12,756 --> 00:43:15,691
Are you getting a lawyer
to go after your daughter?

463
00:43:17,561 --> 00:43:20,086
And have him auction their house?

464
00:43:22,032 --> 00:43:25,900
We don't have to go that far.

465
00:43:27,371 --> 00:43:31,865
How could you lend money
to a man we hardly know?

466
00:43:33,777 --> 00:43:38,737
Money? We simply leased
land we never use.

467
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:42,482
Let's be good, darling.

468
00:43:42,519 --> 00:43:45,511
Now come here and cuddle
your big old polar bear.

469
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:52,152
Stop it!

470
00:44:00,938 --> 00:44:02,838
What do we know about this man?

471
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:05,666
We don't even know
what happened to his wife.

472
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:19,619
- Hello.
- What got into you?

473
00:44:20,324 --> 00:44:21,188
Sjonni.

474
00:44:21,225 --> 00:44:25,161
I travel across
the country to see you

475
00:44:25,195 --> 00:44:26,924
and then you ditch me?

476
00:44:26,964 --> 00:44:29,956
Don't you care
about anyone but yourself?

477
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:33,902
- I have to tell you something.
- What is it?

478
00:44:34,338 --> 00:44:36,932
There is something wrong
with my heart.

479
00:44:36,974 --> 00:44:39,033
It beats so irregularly.

480
00:44:39,076 --> 00:44:40,703
Listen.

481
00:44:45,082 --> 00:44:46,743
You're just too drunk.

482
00:44:49,119 --> 00:44:51,314
Did you hear that?

483
00:44:55,726 --> 00:44:57,921
I could drop dead any moment.

484
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:02,165
What would you do
if I had a heart attack?

485
00:45:07,604 --> 00:45:10,095
What's wrong with the connection
on this godforsaken island!

486
00:45:10,574 --> 00:45:12,872
Just go to the phonespot
and try again.

487
00:45:48,412 --> 00:45:50,004
Sorry, lost the connection.

488
00:45:50,347 --> 00:45:52,679
I'm telling you because
you're my only friend.

489
00:45:53,083 --> 00:45:56,484
You've told me this a hundred times -
and everyone else too.

490
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:57,851
Of course you have
a heart condition.

491
00:45:57,888 --> 00:46:01,085
You're an obese, alcoholic pothead.

492
00:46:01,125 --> 00:46:02,649
Now get some sleep.

493
00:46:02,693 --> 00:46:06,060
We'll get you a doctor tomorrow.

494
00:46:10,634 --> 00:46:12,295
Bloody hell!

495
00:46:47,938 --> 00:46:49,428
Where are you going?

496
00:46:49,473 --> 00:46:51,771
I have to run down
to the guesthouse.

497
00:46:51,809 --> 00:46:53,037
I'll come along.

498
00:46:53,076 --> 00:46:55,510
Just take it easy.
I'll be right back.

499
00:46:55,546 --> 00:46:57,514
I can walk down
to the guesthouse.

500
00:46:59,249 --> 00:47:03,447
All right then, go. Have fun.

501
00:47:05,556 --> 00:47:08,389
I am going to get an extension
on the rent for the golf course.

502
00:47:08,425 --> 00:47:09,449
Not to have fun.

503
00:47:10,127 --> 00:47:13,062
You don't have to justify yourself.
Who's stopping you?

504
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:17,361
Don't be silly, Anna.
I'll be right back.

505
00:47:17,401 --> 00:47:20,268
- Darling, please.
- Please what, my love?

506
00:47:20,604 --> 00:47:23,300
- Don't go.
- Anna...

507
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:27,902
Stay home.
Let's talk, like we used to.

508
00:47:29,346 --> 00:47:32,838
We can cook something.
You can read me your poems.

509
00:47:32,883 --> 00:47:34,373
Please don't go.

510
00:47:34,418 --> 00:47:36,511
- Anna...
- Are you ashamed of me?

511
00:47:36,553 --> 00:47:37,918
No, that's not it.

512
00:47:44,895 --> 00:47:46,123
