but subtract it from Jon's debt,
and give you instead...

775
01:16:43,465 --> 01:16:44,796
a refrigerator.

776
01:16:46,001 --> 01:16:47,298
Why are you doing this?

777
01:16:47,336 --> 01:16:52,706
Because I'm trying
to find a compromise.

778
01:16:53,408 --> 01:16:54,773
We don't need any gifts.

779
01:16:54,810 --> 01:16:56,778
Jon's old refrigerator
works just fine.

780
01:17:01,650 --> 01:17:03,379
Of course we have
to give you something.

781
01:17:03,418 --> 01:17:07,286
We give you the feast
and the refrigerator.

782
01:17:07,322 --> 01:17:10,814
You are obsessed with money.
I didn't ask for any presents...

783
01:17:10,859 --> 01:17:13,851
and we can just skip the feast
if it's such a big deal.

784
01:17:15,464 --> 01:17:17,295
Wouldn't that be just perfect!

785
01:17:17,332 --> 01:17:19,994
I've been preparing
this feast for weeks.

786
01:17:20,035 --> 01:17:21,627
I made twenty kilos
of rhubarb jam.

787
01:17:21,670 --> 01:17:23,934
I don't give a damn!

788
01:17:23,972 --> 01:17:26,202
You don't care about
anything but yourself!

789
01:17:26,241 --> 01:17:30,974
I'm not getting married
to eat your fucking jam!

790
01:17:31,713 --> 01:17:33,704
How do I pee
in this fucking thing!

791
01:17:33,749 --> 01:17:35,114
But why is he marrying you?

792
01:17:35,150 --> 01:17:36,515
Because he loves me!

793
01:17:40,956 --> 01:17:42,423
Coffee, we need coffee.

794
01:17:44,993 --> 01:17:46,654
Where do you keep the coffee?

795
01:17:47,129 --> 01:17:48,562
What am I doing?

796
01:17:49,197 --> 01:17:50,721
What do you mean?

797
01:17:50,766 --> 01:17:52,131
This wedding.

798
01:17:52,734 --> 01:17:57,034
She's almost 20 years younger.
It will never work.

799
01:17:57,673 --> 01:18:00,107
Why are you asking me?

800
01:18:00,142 --> 01:18:02,702
The only woman
I have lived with is my mother.

801
01:18:03,545 --> 01:18:05,103
I can't do it...

802
01:18:09,584 --> 01:18:12,553
Do you realize how lucky you are
to have someone who loves you?

803
01:18:21,163 --> 01:18:23,131
Dear old chap...

804
01:18:24,866 --> 01:18:28,199
I don't care if your wife
is 18 or 80...

805
01:18:28,236 --> 01:18:33,936
if only you promise to be happy
and stop this bloody moaning.

806
01:18:36,044 --> 01:18:38,376
Who the hell
invented the cufflink!

807
01:18:39,848 --> 01:18:42,180
What about
all the money he owes us?

808
01:18:42,217 --> 01:18:46,586
Maybe he's doing this
to get out of the debt?

809
01:18:46,621 --> 01:18:48,646
What do you have
in common after all?

810
01:18:49,391 --> 01:18:52,952
Are you marrying him
just to get back at me?

811
01:18:53,562 --> 01:18:55,291
Can I pee in private?

812
01:18:57,899 --> 01:19:00,993
I give up. I can't do this anymore.

813
01:19:02,003 --> 01:19:04,267
You and your father
bully me around.

814
01:19:04,306 --> 01:19:05,398
Close the door.

815
01:19:05,440 --> 01:19:06,771
You're so pushy!

816
01:19:07,142 --> 01:19:09,110
Jesus!
I'm having a heart attack.

817
01:19:09,144 --> 01:19:11,942
Do that somewhere else,
so I can pee.

818
01:19:15,016 --> 01:19:18,110
- So you're all right with the refrigerator?
- Mom!

819
01:19:28,630 --> 01:19:29,722
Coming!

820
01:19:32,467 --> 01:19:34,435
- What's your shoe size?
- What?

821
01:19:39,374 --> 01:19:40,807
- Malla.
- No.

822
01:19:52,954 --> 01:19:54,251
Where have you been?

823
01:19:56,124 --> 01:19:57,216
Around.

824
01:19:58,994 --> 01:20:01,986
Didn't I tell you
to stay away from Borkur?

825
01:20:02,030 --> 01:20:04,225
- Why?
- What do you mean why?

826
01:20:04,266 --> 01:20:06,427
Why can't I be with Borkur?

827
01:20:06,468 --> 01:20:08,459
It's not good for you.

828
01:20:09,237 --> 01:20:12,206
- Is it because I'm different?
- Malla, darling...

829
01:20:13,241 --> 01:20:14,799
Is it dangerous?

830
01:20:15,777 --> 01:20:18,439
And why can't Thora be with Jon?
Is that also dangerous?

831
01:20:18,480 --> 01:20:20,744
It's better for people
to be with their own kind.

832
01:20:23,118 --> 01:20:25,245
So why can't Lalli be with you?

833
01:20:26,488 --> 01:20:29,389
Is it because he is always
kind and you are...

834
01:20:30,358 --> 01:20:31,757
And I am what?

835
01:20:40,368 --> 01:20:42,336
Yes, thank you.

836
01:20:43,038 --> 01:20:44,300
Did they have my size?

837
01:20:44,339 --> 01:20:47,240
- Yes, they found a pair of shoes.
- Brilliant!

838
01:20:47,275 --> 01:20:49,038
They'll be on the ferry...

839
01:20:49,077 --> 01:20:54,242
and should arrive
just in time for the ceremony.

840
01:20:54,282 --> 01:20:55,476
Great, I love you!

841
01:20:56,751 --> 01:20:58,116
Thanks for the help.

842
01:21:04,292 --> 01:21:07,125
- Isn't that Sjonni?
- It looks like him.

843
01:21:10,031 --> 01:21:11,658
Let's go to the church.

844
01:21:36,157 --> 01:21:38,091
I'm Kristin,
the mother of the groom.

845
01:21:38,126 --> 01:21:39,787
Hi, I'm Sisi.

846
01:21:43,665 --> 01:21:44,962
Oh, my God.

847
01:21:45,634 --> 01:21:48,102
- Where is he?
- He'll be here.

848
01:22:30,512 --> 01:22:34,039
What is she doing on that boat?
Where is she going?

849
01:22:39,821 --> 01:22:41,152
Oh, my God.

850
01:22:56,471 --> 01:22:59,201
We have to get some help.
Hurry!

851
01:23:21,763 --> 01:23:23,060
All right, darling?

852
01:23:41,349 --> 01:23:44,113
The guests are here and
the ceremony is about to start.

853
01:23:44,152 --> 01:23:46,677
Everyone is waiting for you.
Pull yourself together.

854
01:23:53,661 --> 01:23:54,821
No...

855
01:23:56,865 --> 01:23:59,493
What's happening?
Damn!

856
01:24:04,072 --> 01:24:05,539
You have to run!

857
01:24:07,409 --> 01:24:10,207
Don't go! Hey!

858
01:24:10,812 --> 01:24:13,076
Ferry! Don't go!

859
01:24:30,732 --> 01:24:32,791
This has to be a joke.

860
01:25:01,896 --> 01:25:04,421
- She's so young.
- I know.

861
01:25:11,606 --> 01:25:13,233
Do something, Daddy.

862
01:26:10,932 --> 01:26:13,901
I can't do this to you.
Let's step outside.

863
01:26:31,019 --> 01:26:32,577
What the hell are you doing?

864
01:26:32,620 --> 01:26:34,850
- I can't marry you.
- What?

865
01:26:34,889 --> 01:26:36,584
Get right back in there.

866
01:26:36,891 --> 01:26:40,850
Can't this wait
until after the wedding?

867
01:26:40,895 --> 01:26:41,919
Shut up!

868
01:26:42,931 --> 01:26:45,195
I have no right
to ruin your life too.

869
01:26:46,034 --> 01:26:48,161
Since we met
you've aged ten years.

870
01:26:48,203 --> 01:26:49,568
You don't laugh anymore.

871
01:26:50,271 --> 01:26:52,000
Dear guests, just sit still.

872
01:26:52,040 --> 01:26:54,008
The happy couple
has something to discuss.

873
01:26:54,042 --> 01:26:55,600
We are in no hurry.

874
01:26:55,643 --> 01:26:57,235
Nobody is going anywhere.

875
01:26:57,278 --> 01:26:59,838
There isn't another ferry
until tomorrow.

876
01:27:00,915 --> 01:27:02,678
- I've infected you.
- With what?

877
01:27:02,717 --> 01:27:08,246
With boredom, self pity,
anxiety, obsession...

878
01:27:08,790 --> 01:27:11,281
I'm burnt out, a wreck!

879
01:27:13,394 --> 01:27:14,691
Stop it!

880
01:27:14,729 --> 01:27:16,128
A complete burnout!

881
01:27:16,164 --> 01:27:18,291
Maybe we could get some music.

882
01:27:24,372 --> 01:27:29,105
My conscience is bad enough
without ruining your life too.

883
01:27:31,512 --> 01:27:37,917
He's got the gray hair blues,
He's got the gray hair blues

884
01:27:42,557 --> 01:27:44,320
- Don't step on...
- Sorry.

885
01:27:47,328 --> 01:27:48,795
I killed Anna.

886
01:27:52,200 --> 01:27:55,226
I thought that by marrying you...

887
01:27:55,270 --> 01:27:57,397
I could justify what I did to her.

888
01:27:58,773 --> 01:28:03,733
That I did it in the name of love.
For a reason.

889
01:28:04,912 --> 01:28:08,177
- But I'm just not a good man.
- Yes you are.

890
01:28:22,196 --> 01:28:24,289
What's going on?
Everyone is waiting.

891
01:28:24,332 --> 01:28:27,199
- He wants to cancel the wedding.
- What?

892
01:28:32,040 --> 01:28:34,770
You can't do this to us.
Not now.

893
01:28:36,077 --> 01:28:38,978
Do I have to drag you to the altar?

894
01:28:39,013 --> 01:28:41,982
I've said all there is to say.
There won't be any marriage.

895
01:28:42,016 --> 01:28:43,313
Mom, do something!

896
01:28:43,351 --> 01:28:45,785
You can't treat my girl this way.

897
01:28:46,254 --> 01:28:48,381
People are here for a wedding.

898
01:28:48,423 --> 01:28:49,856
If it's because of the money...

899
01:28:49,891 --> 01:28:51,188
What money?

900
01:28:51,225 --> 01:28:53,318
It's not about money,
it's a question of conscience.

901
01:28:53,361 --> 01:28:55,488
What money are you talking about?

902
01:28:55,530 --> 01:28:57,964
The money I gave him
so he could pay you.

903
01:28:57,999 --> 01:29:00,524
- What money did you give him?
- Mom!

904
01:29:00,568 --> 01:29:01,967
What is going on?

905
01:29:02,003 --> 01:29:04,130
He's not doing it. What money?

906
01:29:04,172 --> 01:29:08,131
That's out of the question.
The church is reserved for a wedding

907
01:29:08,176 --> 01:29:09,803
and by God there will be
a wedding in this church today.

908
01:29:09,844 --> 01:29:13,177
Maybe he's hyper-anxious.
He got this as a child.

909
01:29:13,214 --> 01:29:14,841
Answer me!

910
01:29:14,882 --> 01:29:17,112
It's none of your
bloody business, woman!

911
01:29:17,151 --> 01:29:21,986
That's it, this man is
a no-good, irresponsible bastard.

912
01:29:22,023 --> 01:29:24,048
Now you've gone too far.

913
01:29:24,092 --> 01:29:26,890
You don't say this to a man
who's about not to get married.

914
01:29:28,963 --> 01:29:30,931
Don't touch me,
you filthy bastard.

915
01:31:08,663 --> 01:31:09,857
Let me go.

916
01:31:09,897 --> 01:31:11,159
Never.

917
01:31:15,303 --> 01:31:20,263
If it's the last thing I do, I'm going
to get you back on your feet.

918
01:31:21,742 --> 01:31:23,175
Have you settled this?

919
01:31:23,644 --> 01:31:27,011
Bring the bloody priest!
We're doing this here!

920
01:31:50,338 --> 01:31:54,399
I ask you bridegroom,
do you take Thora...

921
01:31:54,442 --> 01:31:58,378
to be your lawful,
wedded wife?

922
01:32:02,016 --> 01:32:03,108
Yes.

923
01:32:04,452 --> 01:32:09,549
- I ask you bride, do you take...
- Yes!

924
01:32:22,403 --> 01:32:24,894
But he shoots himself
at the end of the play.

925
01:32:24,939 --> 01:32:29,171
Does it mean that the love affair
he had wasn't justifiable?

926
01:32:29,210 --> 01:32:31,906
Of course love in itself
is always justifiable.

927
01:32:31,946 --> 01:32:34,506
But it does not justify
our wrongdoings.

928
01:32:35,149 --> 01:32:38,243
So what's the author's point then?

929
01:32:38,286 --> 01:32:40,720
That life offers no simple answers -

930
01:32:40,755 --> 01:32:42,416
just complex questions.

931
01:32:43,991 --> 01:32:49,657
The purpose of life isn't death,
even if it's the end result.

932
01:32:52,567 --> 01:32:59,530
Just as love or happiness isn't
the purpose of life, as such.

933
01:33:00,975 --> 01:33:04,706
Rather the quest.
The quest for love, the quest for happiness.

934
01:33:07,582 --> 01:33:09,106
Hi, darling.

935
01:33:12,587 --> 01:33:14,953
Sorry I'm late. I got held up.

936
01:33:18,893 --> 01:33:20,451
Have you eaten already?

937
01:33:25,900 --> 01:33:27,697
Are you coming along tonight?

938
01:33:35,009 --> 01:33:36,704
Do you feel like going?

939
01:33:44,619 --> 01:33:46,109
I think you should go.

940
01:33:47,555 --> 01:33:49,386
I'm going to stay in and write.

941
01:33:52,627 --> 01:33:57,394
Constant love and happiness
is simply Utopia.

942
01:33:57,431 --> 01:34:01,060
It's much rather something
to be constantly pursued.

943
01:34:02,436 --> 01:34:07,533
If you are completely happy
for more than ten minutes...

944
01:34:07,575 --> 01:34:09,805
you must be an idiot.

